President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. met with Chancellor Angela Merkel and Vice Chancellor Olaf Scholz of Germany to discuss various issues. President Biden congratulated Chancellor Merkel on her 16 years of leadership and their shared focus on security and prosperity. They talked about the situation in Afghanistan, including efforts to provide ongoing humanitarian aid. President Biden also expressed gratitude to Germany for hosting 35,000 Afghan refugees who relocated to the United States. Furthermore, they emphasized the importance of implementing the U.S.-Germany Joint Statement on Support for Ukraine and European Energy Security to prevent Russia from using natural gas flows for harmful political purposes.